******************

A3: Typically 2 days; sometimes 3; can do it in 1 if it is an emergency.

This is part 2 of a 2 part message.

What makes me different from the many other wedding DJs out there?  First of all I always strive to play the proper music for the occasion.  This sounds like a no-brainer but you might be surprised.  When I DJ weddings and receptions I don't play songs that deal with relationships breaking up, cheating, etc. and I stay away from songs with profanity in them so you won't offend anyone who is in attendance.   I'm able to do  this by taking the time to read and categorize the lyrics of the songs that I purchase.  I want everything, including the music, to add to the wonderful feeling that comes with a wedding and not detract from it.

Like other DJs I have thousands of songs available on my laptops, however because I am as careful about profanity as I am, I use radio edit versions when I can.  These version are not readily available to the general public and help me to raise the level enjoyment for everyone.

I love to take requests from the guests.  However I primarily play the genres of music YOU have requested.  I make sure my music library is up to date with the latest releases and have decades of classics to draw from as well.

All my gear is in great working order and I recently upgraded my speakers, subs, microphones, mixer and lights. If you want dance lighting (not up-lighting) I have a nice 4-in-1 dance light that is available at no charge. It does well with smaller dance floors. If you have a larger dance floor or want a wider variety of dance lights you can have my complete dance light system for an additional $150. It can fill an entire gym. If you want the use of a wireless microphone or you want a lapel-type microphone there is no additional charge.

The wedding and reception can be VERY stressful for the bride and groom.  One of my goals is to take away as much of that stress as possible.  The key is communication.  I am a huge advocate of communication.  If I have a clear understanding of what you expect from the DJ and you have a clear understanding of what I will do, things tend to go much more smoothly and less stressful.

Let me be a resource for you.  I have seen many weddings and receptions.  I have seen things that work and things that don't and am happy to share my experience with anyone.  One of my goals is to help take away some of the stress that comes with planning and executing a wedding and reception. If you have questions or would like a little advice with your wedding or reception I would love to help.  I'm not an expert on EVERYTHING but I do know quite a bit.

Safety, integrity, and professionalism are important to us.  We (my wife and I) operate with an actual business license and are fully insured.  That is something not all DJs do so be careful.

I am sending you a copy of my 'Wedding Worksheet' as an attachment to this e-mail.  There is some very good information and ideas towards the end of the Wedding Worksheet that I suggest you look at because you may find it very helpful.  This also gives me much needed information about what it is exactly that you want done during the wedding and reception.  If you need to make changes to the worksheet as the date gets closer it's not a problem.  I am very easy to work with that way.  

My style is simple and fun.  I don't 'scratch' or alter the music when I play it.  At a wedding reception I think more people enjoy dancing to great songs the way they were originally recorded and don't want to hear a DJ 'showing off'.  I am also an in-house DJ for a local wedding reception center ([LOCATION]).  They have seen thousands of receptions and many DJs.  You are more than welcome to call them as a reference.  [PHONE_NUMBER] Ask for [PERSON_NAME] or [PERSON_NAME].

Reviews are VERY important.  They tell you what other clients have thought of the work DJs have done for them and can help you decide if a certain DJ would be a good fit for you or not.  I have many reviews on Thumbtack.com from a variety of clients.  Please take a moment and read a few of them.  It will help give you an idea of the kind of DJ I am and how I would handle an important day like your wedding.

This quote also includes my service as an MC (Master of Ceremonies) at no additional charge.  I am very comfortable behind the microphone but am not too chatty.  This day is NOT about me, it's about you.

I have been married 25 years this summer and I love my wife more now than when we said our vows on our wedding day!  I hope this comes across in my work as a DJ and MC when I work a wedding.  

I look forward to the chance to serve you and helping you make this the wonderful day that it is supposed to be.

[PERSON_NAME] DJ, LLC.

I understand [PERSON_NAME]. There are many different kind of roaches that each have different behaviors. I just want to make sure it is not a german roach issue, which can be a little more difficult to treat. German roaches are an infestation type roach that are smaller than the size of a quarter and commonly found in the kitchen, inside of our appliances and in the bathroom. American, oriental and smokey brown roaches are larger than the size of the quarter and are easily treated with our general pest control.

Here is the information about our general pest control service!
Scorpions and other pest like to nest in the cinder block columns along the back fence. We find that spraying and injecting dust into those columns works wonders for this. We also spray the perimeter of the house and treat all the entry points as well. under the lip of the stucco there are dime sized holes along the J-trim. Easy access for roaches and scorpions to crawl into and nest in between the wall voids and eventually find their way inside your home through ceiling vents, plumbing, or outlets. Most pests including roaches only need 1/64th of an inch to get through. We will also inject a dust in those holes to flush out pests and create a long lasting barrier. We spray a barrier around the perimeter of the home for those Flies and all other insects such as earwigs, silverfish, roaches etc you name it. Then, we spot treat the rest of the entire yard and looking for the black widow webs and ant piles and treat as necessary and target areas like palm trees. We also will use a 25' pole to de-web any spider webs and wasp nests in the eaves around the home and in the garage. We apply granules to any grass to take care of fleas and ticks as well. The inside only needs to be done once a year. The initial service flushes out the adult pests then we do a follow up service 30-45 days later to treat all the baby cockraoches and other bugs to get a jump start on the process. The outside is done every 2 months thereafter with FREE reservices in between in the event you see any bugs in between treatments. We have your house guaranteed bug free with a money back guarantee. As far as the price goes, usually the initial is $199 and $89 every other month. Since we have spots available for tomorrow and early next week what day would work best for you? We can do the initial for just $39 and only $69.00 every two months thereafter. All products are high quality and are kid and pet safe and your only spending about a dollar a day

I was at the Sunset Market all day, and just now got back to review some bids.  While it's late, I wanted to get this to you as soon as possible for your review.  Please note that while you did request drop off, I listed this as a partial service (staff there to maintain your buffet).  While most companies would be more than happy to simply drop the food off and move on, figuring the problem is yours to maintain temperature on the food and keep it safe, we want your event to be a success!  For the number of guests you plan to have, you will have quite a few food trays not currently being served in chafer dishes, sitting around, getting cold.  If we have staff on-site, they can maintain/replace food trays as they go empty, and they will also have our equipment with them, designed to keep food hot for 4+ hours while sitting in storage, waiting to be served.  The difference in cost to you is minimal, but the difference in food quality and food safety is much greater.

With that all said, we were still able to keep the price on the low side of your price request, at $20.65/person.  We based the bid on 125 people, but can of course, adjust accordingly.  We also assumed everyone having at least some of each dish.  When you are at a brewery with alcohol flowing, people tend to eat more than usual, which is why we did 125 portions of each appetizer.  Let me know if you'd like me to adjust the bid, and I'd be more than happy to accommodate you any way you wish!

We look forward to seeing you at our food booth next week as well!  If you have any questions, feel free to give me a call, or send me a response here.  I'll get back to you as soon as possible!

P.S. Did you need disposable plates, flatware, and napkins with this order?  You did not specify if you needed any additional supplies, so I wasn't sure if you were handling this yourself, or needed us to supply it for you.

[PERSON_NAME],

Thank you for the response. 

I do have a few stuffed animals and letter blocks that I bring along for these shoots. Usually I try to get at least one photo that incorporates the blocks, usually with the little one's name or birthdate. 

If you have an available bassinet or crib, we can incorporate that as well. 

I also, always bring a new stuffed animal for the kids to keep. With infants, it's not as important. But with older children, they usually respond better to instructions, knowing they're receiving something in exchange for cooperation. 

As for poses, I like to keep it simple when it comes to infants and toddlers. Some of the poses I like to do include a photo with blocks(mentioned above), a close up photo of the feet, a close up of baby being held by mom/dad(resting on chest) or of baby holding mom/dad's hand, and of course a close up of baby's upper body and face. 

In addition to those poses, there's always room for impromptu poses and parental suggestions as well. After all, these photos are your memories. 

If you'd like to book a session, I can get you on the books. For a project this size, there is no deposit. I simply ask that you notify me 24 hours in advance if you decide to cancel.
